<br>
eMac Feature List
<font face=Chicago/12 color=#ffffff>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<p align=50%>
MacBar with working Apple and Task Menus<br>
User-customizable Applications menu<br>
15 diffrent border styles<br>
Full MacOS widget set<br>
Epplet and Eterm automode support<br>
Color schemes:<br>
BondiBlue, BlueBerry, Grape,<br>
Strawberry, Tangerine, and Lime<br>



<page columns=1 padding=16 name=macbar background=Edoc_bg.jpg linkcolor=#edeeff>
<p align=50%>
<font face=Chicago/20 color=#ffffff>
<br>
The MacBar
<font face=Chicago/12 color=#ffffff>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<p align=50%>
When you first start eMac, you will notice a grey bar at the top of the screen. This is
the MacBar, eMac's equivalent of the MacOS menu bar. While the menus on this bar will not
change with the application, they do provide you with several very useful functions. The
MacBar is permanent and not moveable or removable. To open a menu on the MacBar, click and
hold the mouse button on a menu. Release the mouse button to clear the menu.



<page columns=1 padding=16 name=applemenu background=Edoc_bg.jpg linkcolor=#edeeff>
<p align=50%>
<font face=Chicago/20 color=#ffffff>
<br>
The Apple Menu
<font face=Chicago/12 color=#ffffff>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<p align=50%>
The apple menu in eMac is very customizable. There are several diffrent icons
available. The standard icon, an icon matching the default theme, and one for
each of the color schemes.



